This will popup a dialog with "ja" and "nej" buttons. If the user clicks "ja", the window.print() method will be called to print the page.

The native `confirm` dialog in JavaScript does not allow customization of button labels; it will always show "OK" and "Cancel". To create a custom dialog with "ja" and "nej", you can use HTML and JavaScript. Here’s an example implementation:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="da">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <title>Print Invoice</title>
    <style>
        #customConfirm {
            display: none;
            position: fixed;
            top: 50%;
            left: 50%;
            transform: translate(-50%, -50%);
            background: white;
            border: 1px solid #ccc;
            padding: 20px;
            z-index: 1000;
        }
        #overlay {
            display: none;
            position: fixed;
            top: 0;
            left: 0;
