To create a more polished and integrated experience for your confirmation dialog, you can use libraries like **SweetAlert2** or **Bootstrap Modal**. Below is an example using **SweetAlert2**, which provides a nice pop-up dialog with customizable options.

### Example Using SweetAlert2

1. **Include SweetAlert2**:
   First, include the SweetAlert2 library in your HTML:

   ```html
   <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/sweetalert2@11/dist/sweetalert2.min.css">
   <script src="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/sweetalert2@11"></script>
   ```

2. **JavaScript Function**:
   Use the following JavaScript function to create the confirmation dialog:

   ```html
   <script>
   function printInvoice() {
       Swal.fire({
           title: 'Vil du udskrive fakturaen?',
           showCancelButton: true,
           confirmButtonText: 'ja',
           cancelButtonText: 'nej',
       }).then((result) => {
           if (result.isConfirmed) {
               window.print();
           }
       });
   }
   </script>
   ```

3. **HTML Button**:
   Create a button to trigger the printing process:

   ```html
   <button onclick="printInvoice()">Print Invoice</button>
   ```

### Full Example

Here’s how everything fits together:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="da">
